    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/community-coffee-corner-blog-posts/my-sapphire-orlando-2025-recap-from-an-sap-community-point-of-view/ba-p/14114822</id>
    <title>My Sapphire Orlando 2025 recap from an SAP Community point of view</title>
    <updated>2025-05-29T20:58:29.282000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>josh_bentley</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/148</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P class=""&gt;Hi everybody!&amp;nbsp; Mr. &lt;FONT color="#0000FF"&gt;bluebeard&lt;/FONT&gt; here and I wanted to give you a recap of my experience at this year's SAP Sapphire 2025 event in Orlando, Florida.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;The Show Floor&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;When I got to Orlando, it was a lot like coming home because I've been to several Sapphires but there's nothing like that feeling when you approach the Orange County Convention Center and you know that you're about to go through an amazing entranceway and see a beautiful show floor.&amp;nbsp; Well, that's what happened.&amp;nbsp; The SAP team designed an amazing show entrance that was very photo worthy.&amp;nbsp; The show floor had lots of vendor and partner booths to the left, and a keynote stage auditorium to the right as well as a broadcast studio for virtual attendee presentations.&amp;nbsp; Along the sides we several large and small theaters for dedicated deep dive presentations, and a meeting center in the back.&amp;nbsp; There were several areas to relax and take phone calls as well, but most amazing to me was the center hallway of the show floor.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="entrance before escalator down" style="width: 316px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267505i18B29A7D97E4D721/image-dimensions/316x421?v=v2" width="316" height="421" role="button" title="entrance before escalator.jpeg" alt="entrance before escalator down" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;entrance before escalator down&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="show floor main walkway" style="width: 314px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267504iEC0BDDBC600558C4/image-dimensions/314x419?v=v2" width="314" height="419" role="button" title="sapphire_entrance_floor.jpeg" alt="show floor main walkway" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;show floor main walkway&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;The center hallway started off with the SAP Experience Center, which I'm part of in Team SIX (Solution, Industries and Experience), the SIX team is responsible for designing and giving people a great experience going through all the innovations that SAP software is enabling. For this Experience Center you queued up outside like you were waiting at an amusement park and then you enter and you are informed about the persona journey that you're about to partake in, much like you would at an SAP Experience Center at an SAP office.&amp;nbsp; You pick a role like CEO, CPO, CHRO, then you get a AirTag that syncs to an Android or an iPhone so you can browse all the learnings on your mobile if you didn't have time to complete everything in the Experience Center.&amp;nbsp; They brought in a industrial injection machine, a warehouse robot set up to show how you could repair that equipment if it broke using AI. Once you get done in the experience center and you exit the enclosed area you're in the center hallway again.&amp;nbsp; You see a lot of beautiful booths with experts from BTP, Applications and a lot of people that are just having conversations with our customers and partners about SAP technology.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="experience center" style="width: 269px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267506i7E8B9015B54663A4/image-dimensions/269x359?v=v2" width="269" height="359" role="button" title="experience center.jpeg" alt="experience center" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;experience center&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="experience center guided tour" style="width: 475px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267512i83198C81685A038D/image-dimensions/475x356?v=v2" width="475" height="356" role="button" title="experience center 2.jpeg" alt="experience center guided tour" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;experience center guided tour&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="airtag delivery robot arm" style="width: 321px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267511iC5FCB5A165C69AB8/image-dimensions/321x428?v=v2" width="321" height="428" role="button" title="experience center 3.jpeg" alt="airtag delivery robot arm" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;airtag delivery robot arm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;Then when you reach the back edge of the hallway before you get to the meeting event center that's where you see the great Learning and Certification Lab. We had a 25 person auditorium theater built into it, several different touch panels where you could choose to take a picture of yourself and have AI generate a graphic image of you tied to your user name. After completing quizzes your image &amp;amp; name were listed on a leaderboard for all to see.&amp;nbsp; But also as you tapped your badge at the monitors and completed knowledge exercises you accumulated learning power and the tree of learning would glow brighter the more you learned.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Andre Bechtold preso in Lab" style="width: 433px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267517iAFF9DF7A1D9CB5F4/image-dimensions/433x325?v=v2" width="433" height="325" role="button" title="andre speaking theater.jpeg" alt="Andre Bechtold preso in Lab" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;Andre Bechtold preso in Lab&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="leaderboard" style="width: 244px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267516i11A4E7FC77C086E7/image-dimensions/244x325?v=v2" width="244" height="325" role="button" title="leaderboard.jpeg" alt="leaderboard" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;leaderboard&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Learning and Certification Lab" style="width: 386px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267515i7F17470D425C9F62/image-dimensions/386x290?v=v2" width="386" height="290" role="button" title="learning and certification lab.jpeg" alt="Learning and Certification Lab" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;Learning and Certification Lab&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Sitting area outside lab" style="width: 383px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267518iADEA0B4371E0DF10/image-dimensions/383x287?v=v2" width="383" height="287" role="button" title="sitting area.jpeg" alt="Sitting area outside lab" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;Sitting area outside lab&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="tree of learning" style="width: 330px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267519i5DC67E512CFCDF3E/image-dimensions/330x440?v=v2" width="330" height="440" role="button" title="tree of knowledge.jpeg" alt="tree of learning" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;tree of learning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;Now onto what I did while in the space.&amp;nbsp; In the theater at the back of the Learning and Certification Lab is where myself and one of our SAP mentors &lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/5526"&gt;@DanielleLarocca&lt;/a&gt;, as well as &lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/192605"&gt;@anita_riegel&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;from team SIX all got together and presented in a panel format "How to Harness the Power of the SAP Community".&amp;nbsp; It was a 25 minute chat to explain to people what the SAP community is and how they can benefit from it because it's their community.&amp;nbsp; Everyone who was sitting in that room was a member of the community just by being there.&amp;nbsp; Maybe they don't use the website, so we directed them&amp;nbsp;to &lt;A href="http://community.sap.com" target="_self"&gt;community.sap.com&lt;/A&gt; and how they can use those resources once signed up, but also being present at Sapphire, SAP TechEd, SAP Inside Tracks, Meetups and attending things like an an SAP CodeJam allow for community interaction in person, around the world.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="community session pic 1.jpeg" style="width: 338px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267523i1B4FA5CD7FDE3965/image-dimensions/338x253?v=v2" width="338" height="253" role="button" title="community session pic 1.jpeg" alt="community session pic 1.jpeg" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="community session selfie.jpeg" style="width: 338px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267522i50DC695B38C76288/image-dimensions/338x254?v=v2" width="338" height="254" role="button" title="community session selfie.jpeg" alt="community session selfie.jpeg" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;Also I just met and talked with people outside of the SAP learning certification lab when I wasn't in a meeting.&amp;nbsp; Speaking of meetings, a lot of my time was spent working with people that are part of the SAP Mentors and Champions programs, enjoying conversations with them about what we can do to make our community experiences better.&amp;nbsp; They met with SAP executives and leaders within several SAP organizations and expressed direct feedback, so it was very nice to be a part of those meetings along with &lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/109"&gt;@StephanieMarley&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;Then I went to a meeting with the &lt;A href="https://apphaus.sap.com/partner/network" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;SAP AppHaus&lt;/A&gt; team, and learned more about their network of SAP AppHaus locations and what they're doing with the partner network to expand the reach of the AppHaus methodology and how we can host things like a CodeJam, or do other customer events inside of these AppHaus locations which are optimized to take people through the SAP AppHaus methodology for solving their business problems.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="AppHaus meeting" style="width: 370px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267531i6FFD12A1A7AF4299/image-dimensions/370x494?v=v2" width="370" height="494" role="button" title="apphaus meeting.jpeg" alt="AppHaus meeting" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;AppHaus meeting&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;My Favorite Moment&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;I met a lot of new friends as well at after hours events like the AWS Networking Session. One was a gentleman from Mexico, Adrian, who works for a lighting industry company.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;It was honestly my favorite moment because I got to hear his story about what it was like to attend Sapphire in Philadelphia (where i live) in 1996 as well as SAP TechEd that year, so really cool stories comparing not only those early events but the changes to the software we are presenting now that his company utilizes.&amp;nbsp; Adrian has been around for a long time and he has seen the change of SAP software as well as the differences between on premise and cloud, and now the integration of AI and how businesses utilize that software.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="aws networking.jpeg" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267524i23FD28AB815C9B1D/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="aws networking.jpeg" alt="aws networking.jpeg" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;The Keynotes&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;The keynotes were great from a high level. I attended all the keynote sessions at the keynote theater, which is a large space on the show floor that was full, even into the stadium seating outside.&amp;nbsp; Seeing all the great presentations with the things that we're doing from all the executives was awesome, but seeing a friend of mine, Abishek, from the old SAP mobile team who is now moved through his career up to the point where he's working for NBC Universal and was one of the customers on stage presenting how they are using all these great things was so fun and rewarding to see.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;A few of the &lt;A href="https://news.sap.com/2025/05/sap-business-ai-reimagine-how-enterprises-run/" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;announcements&lt;/A&gt; from the keynotes:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Intelligent Apps for the SAP Business Data Cloud&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Joule AI assistant availability&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Perplexity partnership&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;AI Foundation&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;many more....&amp;nbsp;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="keynote selfie" style="width: 312px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267525i5E9E7193BA4F0B7A/image-dimensions/312x416?v=v2" width="312" height="416" role="button" title="keynote 1.jpeg" alt="keynote selfie" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;keynote selfie&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Thomas Saueressig at keynote" style="width: 429px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267526iA018A66B2444294A/image-dimensions/429x321?v=v2" width="429" height="321" role="button" title="keynote 2.jpeg" alt="Thomas Saueressig at keynote" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;Thomas Saueressig at keynote&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="overflow seating" style="width: 562px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267527iD3C13345AC758A8C/image-dimensions/562x421?v=v2" width="562" height="421" role="button" title="keynote outside seating.jpeg" alt="overflow seating" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;overflow seating&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Celebration Night&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;Then we had a great event at Disney's Epcot Center Park where SAP entertained everyone who came to Sapphire by renting out the entire park.&amp;nbsp; We had two opportunities to listen to some music from the concert artist, The Zac Brown Band, and just if you wanted to ride rides or enter into any of the different country themed sections of Epcot Park you could do that.&amp;nbsp; There were several places to grab food, snacks, drinks, and just talk to all your friends and colleagues from SAP.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;It was a nice night, but a little humid as Florida tends to be. I made it halfway around the world...&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Epcot entrance" style="width: 300px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267529i55C242248E598AAB/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="epcot 1.jpeg" alt="Epcot entrance" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;Epcot entrance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Zac Brown" style="width: 225px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267528i09D66B1681B1ACE0/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="epcot 2.jpeg" alt="Zac Brown" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;Zac Brown&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Epcot at night" style="width: 300px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267530iF69A571AB1C80C3F/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="epcot 3.jpeg" alt="Epcot at night" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;Epcot at night&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;   &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;In Summary&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;Finally flying home after a long week of meetings and having great interactions with all the people on the show floor reminds me it is such an honor to get to do what I do.&amp;nbsp; As I like to say, I have a "get to job".&amp;nbsp; I get to do this!&amp;nbsp; And I enjoyed reflecting by looking at the tons of pictures that I took, especially for the &lt;A href="https://community.sap.com/t5/community-coffee-corner-blog-posts/2025-sapphire-selfies-with-bluebeard/ba-p/14105283" target="_self"&gt;Selfies with bluebeard post&lt;/A&gt;, Well over 30 people commented on my beard which was so great cause I used that as an ice breaker to get a pic.&amp;nbsp; I know &lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/29"&gt;@moshenaveh&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;has asked other people attending Sapphire to write up their experiences from this year's Sapphire and I look forward to reading those recaps.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P class=""&gt;It was a certifiably good time.&amp;nbsp; Hope to see you at the next event.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="who, what, where?!?" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/267533i60E9E4C9A4A0BD3F/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="selfie with characters.jpeg" alt="who, what, where?!?" /&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-caption" onclick="event.preventDefault();"&gt;who, what, where?!?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt; &lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/community-coffee-corner-blog-posts/my-sapphire-orlando-2025-recap-from-an-sap-community-point-of-view/ba-p/14114822"/>
    <published>2025-05-29T20:58:29.282000+02:00</published>
